---
title: Crispy Parmesan Chicken with Garlic Scallion Couscous & Lemony Roasted Broccoli
description: Consider plain chicken a thing of the past. In this recipe, the cutlets get gussied up thanks to a gorgeous golden breadcrumb topping with paprika and Parmesan cheese. You’ll roast them alongside the lemony carrots on the same baking sheet—once they’re in the oven, the only thing left to do is boil the pearl couscous and toss it with the garlicky butter. Simple, satisfying, and supercharged with flavor—what more could you ask for?
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6447d0dce462b535dd06af22-ec924ae9.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64f8cd0bf6dcf759f5e611fe.pdf
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/crispy-parmesan-chicken-64f8cd0bf6dcf759f5e611fe
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 40 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 650 kcal
  fat: 32 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 51 g
  sugar: 6 g
  protein: 45 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 360 mg
course: main course
---

  Adjust rack to middle position (middle and top positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and halve @Carrots{12%ounce}; cut crosswise into 2-inch-long pieces. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

Cut @Broccoli Florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. (Save carrots for another use.)

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Parmesan Cheese{3%tablespoon}, @Hot Smoked Paprika{1%teaspoon}, a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{4%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Place on one side of a #baking sheet{} (for 4 servings, arrange across entire sheet).

Spread tops of chicken with @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon}. Mound with panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Toss carrots on opposite side of sheet from chicken with a large drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, toss carrots on a second baking sheet.)

Roast on middle rack until chicken is cooked through and carrots are browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. (For 4, roast chicken on middle rack and carrots on top rack.)

> If carrots are done before chicken, remove from sheet and continue roasting chicken.

Swap in broccoli for carrots; roast for ~{12-15%minutes}. Remove broccoli from sheet and continue roasting chicken until cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} more.

While chicken and carrots roast, add @Israeli Couscous{2.5%ounce} to #pot{} with boiling water. Cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Drain thoroughly.

Melt @Butter{2%tablespoon} (3 TBSP for 4 servings) in empty pot over medium heat. Add scallion whites and garlic; cook until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Return cooked couscous to pot and stir until coated. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Once carrots are done roasting, carefully toss with lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste.

Divide chicken, carrots, and couscous between plates. Garnish chicken with scallion greens. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.